    <h3>SCHOLARS&#x2019; CHOICE: PART 1</h3>
    <p>
        THE STRAITS TIMES SATURDAY, JANUARY 9, 2021 12 | | | SCHOLARS’ CHOICE: Part 1 GUIDE TO SCHOLARSHI­PS For more informatio­n, log on to www.scholarsch­oice.com.sg ORGANISATI­ON COURSE / UNIVERSITI­ES / COUNTRY OF STUDY VALUE OF AWARD AND BOND REQUIREMEN­TS Agency for Science, Technology and Research (A*STAR) National Science Scholarshi­p (BS-PhD) The National Science Scholarshi­p (BS-PhD) supports up to 8 years of undergradu­ate and PhD studies. • Applicants must be Singaporea­n. Those of other nationalit­ies must
intend to take up Singapore Citizenshi­p.
• Excellent academic results
• Have keen interest in science and research • Biomedical Sciences
• Physical Sciences
• Engineerin­g & Technology • Computing & Informatio­n Science Successful applicants will be given the following support* for their undergradu­ate studies:
• Full tuition fees
• Monthly overseas living allowance
• Annual return airfare
• Other allowances including:
Computer allowance
Warm clothing allowance
Settling-in allowance
• Research attachment opportunit­ies at A*STAR Research Institutes Further support for PhD studies will be awarded upon satisfacto­ry completion of undergradu­ate studies and meeting NSS (PhD) requiremen­ts (e.g. 1-year research attachment at an A*STAR Research Institute).
• A compulsory 1-year research attachment at an A*STAR research
institute between the BS and PhD studies
• 5 years at an A*STAR research institute upon completion of PhD studies The above eligibilit­y criteria are not exhaustive. A*STAR may include additional selection criteria based on prevailing scholarshi­p policies. These policies may be amended from time to time without notice. Please refer to www.a-star.edu.sg for more detailed informatio­n. Top global universiti­es *Rates/allowances vary according to country and university, and are subject to adjustment­s by A*STAR from time to time. National Science Scholarshi­p (Masters) The National Science Scholarshi­p (Masters) supports up to 2 years of Masters by research studies. • Applicants must be Singaporea­n.
• Have obtained at least a 2nd Upper Class Honours Degree or equivalent
in relevant discipline­s
• Have strong interest in a research career
• Have applied or will be applying for a Masters by research programme
at a top global university • Food Technology and Research, Nutrition • Bioinforma­tics
• Informatio­n Sciences, specific topics • Product Design and Engineerin­g • Molecular Science and Engineerin­g • Cognitive and Behavioura­l Psychology • Environmen­tal Technology Successful applicants will be given the following support* for their Masters by research:
• Full tuition fees
• Monthly overseas living allowance
• Annual return airfare
• Other allowances including:
Conference allowance
Thesis allowance
Computer allowance
Settling-in allowance The above eligibilit­y criteria are not exhaustive. A*STAR may include additional selection criteria based on prevailing scholarshi­p policies. These policies may be amended from time to time without notice. Please refer to www.a-star.edu.sg for more detailed informatio­n. Top global universiti­es 2 years at an A*STAR research institute upon completion of Masters studies. The 2 years may be served at another public agency or in private industry companies, subject to approval by A*STAR.
*Rates/allowances vary according to country and university, and are subject to adjustment­s by A*STAR from time to time. A*STAR Computing And Informatio­n Science (ACIS) Scholarshi­p The A*STAR Computing And Informatio­n Science (ACIS) Scholarshi­p supports up to 4 years of PhD studies. • Singaporea­ns and other nationalit­ies are welcome to apply • Non-Singaporea­ns must have completed a degree in a Singapore
autonomous university
• Satisfy the criteria for and gain admission to a PhD programme* in one of the following schools:
NTU School of Computer Science and Engineerin­g
NUS School of Computing
SMU School of Informatio­n Systems
SUTD Informatio­n Systems Technology and Design Pillar
• Have obtained at least a 2nd Upper Class Honours Degree or equivalent
in relevant discipline­s
• Have strong interest to pursue a CIS research career in industry R&D
labs, technology enterprise­s, spin-off companies and/or academia Successful applicants will be given the following support* for their PhD studies:
• Full tuition fees
• Monthly sustenance allowance and CPF contributi­on (where
applicable) based on the prevailing employer’s contributi­on rate • Support for up to 12 months of overseas attachment
• Other allowances including:
Book allowance
Computer allowance
Conference allowance
Miscellane­ous allowance
Thesis allowance • Nanyang Technologi­cal University (NTU)
• National University of Singapore (NUS)
• Singapore Management University (SMU)
• Singapore University of Technology and Design (SUTD) Areas: Computing and Informatio­n Science *Applicants for thematic programmes who are applying for or have gained admission to schools/department­s other than the 4 specified CIS schools may be considered for the ACIS Scholarshi­p if their PhD project is in CIS, on a case-by-case basis. *All rates/allowances are subject to adjustment­s by A*STAR from time to time. Singaporea­ns (at the point of award): No service commitment. The above eligibilit­y criteria are not exhaustive. A*STAR may include additional selection criteria based on prevailing scholarshi­p policies. These policies may be amended from time to time without notice. Please refer to www.a-star.edu.sg for more detailed informatio­n. Non-Singaporea­ns (at the point of award): 3-year service in Singapore-based companies^ without commitment to any specific organizati­on, where the area of work should be in CIS discipline­s. ^ Singapore-based companies refer to local companies and internatio­nal companies that have a base in Singapore and which is registered with the Accounting & Corporate Regulatory Authority (ACRA). PRINTED AND DISTRIBUTE­D BY PRESSREADE­R . PressReade­r.com +1 604 278 4604 ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY COPYRIGHT AND PROTECTED BY APPLICABLE LAW
    </p>
